  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">Svenska R&#xF6;da Korset, partnerskap mellan HRFT och SRC 2021-2024</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Swedish Red Cross, partnership between HRFT and SRC 2021-2024</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">Svenska R&#xF6;da Korset har s&#xF6;kt medel fr&#xE5;n Sida p&#xE5; 1 058 130 SEK f&#xF6;r att genomf&#xF6;ra projektet Partnerskap mellan HRFT och SRK 2021-2024 under perioden  2021-2024.

Projektet &#xE4;r ett kunskapsutbyte mellan Svenska R&#xF6;da Korset i Sverige, den enhet som jobbar med tortyr och flyktingverksamhet och HRFT i Turkiet, en CSO som arbetar med tortyr &#xF6;verlevare och deras n&#xE4;rst&#xE5;ende och deras rehalilitering i Turkiet. Programmet kommer huvudsakligen fokusera p&#xE5; metoder relaterade till klinisk, psykosocial, socialt arbete, preventering av sekund&#xE4;r trauma. D&#xE4;r experter inom omr&#xE5;dena kommer utbyta erfarenheter och kunskap. Det kommer bla ske genom 4 st &#xE5;rliga utbytetillf&#xE4;llen i Sverige eller i Turkiet, d&#xE4;r anst&#xE4;llda fr&#xE5;n b&#xE5;da organisationerna kommer delta.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Swedish Red Cross has applied for funding from Sida of SEK 1,058,130 to implement the project Partnership between HRFT and SRK 2021-2024 during the period 2021-2024.

The project is an exchange of knowledge between the Swedish Red Cross in Sweden, the unit that works with torture and refugee activities and HRFT in Turkey, a CSO that works with torture survivors and their relatives and their rehabilitation in Turkey. The program will mainly focus on methods related to clinical, psychosocial, social work, prevention of secondary trauma. Where experts in the fields will exchange experiences and knowledge. This will take place, among other things, through 4 annual exchange opportunities in Sweden or in Turkey, where employees from both organizations will participate.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen social and psychosocial rehabilitation of torture survivors and refugees through professional development of HRFT and SRC care givers.</narrative>
  </description>
